    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 3.5: ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL POSITION SENSOR/IVS SWITCH (APS/IVS) - CRUISE CONTROL, PTO, HAND THROTTLE SYSTEM - FAULT
        DETECTION MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>The ECM monitors the SCCS signals for proper voltages and will set flash code 221. If the ignition switch
            is turned off, the fault will be recorded as an inactive fault.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="BOLD">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f19017112">3.92</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the cruise control, PTO and hand throttle circuit diagram and
            <emph type="BOLD">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="f19017113">3.32</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the connector checks.
        </para>
        <figure id="f19017112" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1250" filename="../figeg1/EG1250.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.92 Cruise Control, PTO And Hand Throttle Circuit Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
